<%- include('partials/header') %>
<main class="container">
  <div class="page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">Backup</p>
    <h1>Export &amp; import</h1>
    <p class="lead">One file with everything worth never losing: every page/section/variant,
      every short link's current file, redirect history for renamed slugs — <strong>and the
      file bytes themselves</strong> for anything on local storage. Excludes users, sessions,
      and storage credentials.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Export</h2>
    <p class="muted small">Downloads a single <code>.zip</code>: <code>manifest.json</code>
      (taxonomy + link/slug map) plus a <code>files/</code> folder with every local-driver
      file's actual bytes. Bunny/S3-backed files are listed in the manifest but not bundled —
      their bytes already live on that storage, independent of this app.</p>
    <a class="btn primary" href="/api/admin/export" download>Export files + link map (.zip)</a>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Import</h2>
    <p class="muted small">Restores from an exported <code>.zip</code> (or a legacy map-only
      <code>.json</code>). <strong>Never overwrites</strong> a slug, taxonomy entry, or file
      already on disk — only adds what's missing, so it's safe to run against a live database.
      Bunny/S3-backed links are restored as metadata only; their bytes are wherever they were
      originally uploaded.</p>
    <div class="row wrap">
      <input type="file" id="importFile" accept=".zip,.json,application/zip,application/json" />
      <button class="btn primary" id="importBtn">Import</button>
    </div>
    <div id="importMsg" class="msg"></div>
    <div id="importSummary" class="hidden"></div>
  </section>
</main>
<script src="/public/admin-backup.js"></script>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
